        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-09-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-09-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="231"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                <head>231. Telegram USITO 51 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d231fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/9–2355. Confidential.
                        Drafted by Meiklejohn; cleared in USIA by Hutchinson, Zorthian, and Stephens
                        and by <persName corresp="#p_LJMH_1">Lindbeck</persName>, and <persName
                            corresp="#p_MWP_1">McConaughy</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1955-09-23">September 23, 1955, 6:36 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d231-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d231-1"/>
                <p>USITO 51. Joint State-USIA Message. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1"
                        >Johnson</persName> and Garnish.</p>
                <p>View criticalness Geneva talks, Garnish stories for wireless file will be
                    accepted here as definitive subjected no editing that may distort meaning on
                    understanding clearance Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1"
                        >Johnson</persName> obtained all items filed on Talks.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Streibert</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
